  "texts": [
    "Evidence that people consume information that aligns with their existing beliefs and attitudes, posited by selective exposure theory, emerges from our results as users on different platforms gravitated towards discussing aspects of ChatGPT that interest them or align with their perspective.",
    "Moreover, the agenda-setting theory suggests that the media significantly influences what issues are important to the public based on the coverage they receive.",
    "The heightened discussion around ChatGPT across all platforms following its release is a classic example of this theory in play.",
    "Lastly, the importance of framing is also evident in our research.",
    "How topics related to LLMs and COVID-19 vaccines are presented on different platforms can significantly affect perceptions and resultant user engagements."
  ],
